title: For Sale:  STI Tactical 5.0 2011 9mm
postcontent:
Barely used STI Tactical 5.0 chambered in 9mm

For a general description go to STIguns.com

I bought this gun used with less than 1,000 rounds through it. I have ran less than 200 thru it. It has been well cared for and comes with a lot of extras. The gun was cleaned after every range session. Here are some specs:

Barrel(s): The gun comes with 2 barrels, the stock STI bull barrel and a Storm Lake extended and threaded barrel. The thread pitch is 13.5x1MM LH. The only reason I had it threaded in that pitch was the suppressor I had on order had a booster with the metric threads from the factory. I never planned on using my can on another handgun, that’s why I didn’t go with the 1/2x28 on the barrel and buy another piston from AAC. ¾ of the total rounds have been through the threaded barrel. I’ve only shot FMJ ammo out of both barrels. The threaded barrel was fitted by a certified gunsmith. The Storm Lake barrel comes with a thread protector. It was special order from Storm Lake since 5” 1911 bull barrels in 9x19 with metric threads aren’t that common…

Sights: The sights are Trijicon Heine night sights. The front and rear both glow green- one dot up front, one dot in the rear. Rear sight is serrated.

Grip: Grip has been stippled and has a great feel. It does gives more control without being overly aggressive. I left the area under/around the trigger guard untouched. If you wanted to replace it you can easily get a brand new grip with mainspring housing for $115 from Shooters Connection. The magwell is the STI 2011 aluminum magwell.

Internals: Gunsmith installed a Cylinder and Slide 1911 24/7/365 Professional 5lb. trigger pull set (http://www.cylinder-slide.com/index....how&ref=CS0324). It makes for a crisp, clean break. I also had an STI gunsmith blank flat trigger installed. I will include all the stock parts that came in the gun.

Holsters: I will also include a Safariland 6280-5621, a COM (center of mass) kydex holster and a Bladetech single magazine pouch. The Safariland is light-compatible. I bought it for use with a Streamlight TLR-2. The belt loops are 2”. The COM holster is not light compatible and has 1.5” belt loops (I bought if for use with an Ares gear Ranger belt). The Bladetech will fit 1.75” belts. All 3 are adjustable for tension. All are for right-handed shooters. Both holsters will accommodate the extended threaded barrel.

Magazines: I will include 4 magazines: 3 flush-fit 126mm mags (17 round) and one 170mm (26 round) mag. I did use a paint pen to mark the basepads with numbers and my initials (easily removed). Most importantly the mags have been tuned. They all have the stock basepads, followers and springs, but the feed lips have been adjusted for the gun. Originally I had feeding issues with some of the mags when shooting suppressed. The feed lips were to blame. STI mags can be finicky, but I’ve shot all 4 of these suppressed and unsuppressed and haven’t had any problems. Tuned mags can go for over $100 a piece so if you throw on a Dawson basepad/follower you’ll have some competition-ready mags.


Other: The mag release, ambi safety and slide release are stock. The gun has the stock Recoil Master guide rod/spring.

Asking $2,650 but will entertain any serious offer. The gun has to go. I've changed the class I plan to shoot in USPSA and have no use for this pistol. It's a great gun and will make someone very happy.

If you have any questions or want to make me an offer or want more pictures, feel free to email me at REDACTED or PM me.

I'll ship to your FFL or meet FTF near Pittsburgh at FFL. 

Only partial trade interests currently are - S&W PC 357 8 shot revolvers, CZ 75 Target Shadow 9mm, FS2000, PS90, Savage model 12.

Thanks!

title: For Sale:   ZASTAVA M57 7.62x25 PISTOL with EXTRA MAG (NIB!)
postcontent:
Manufacturer: Zastava
Model: M57
Caliber: 7.62x25

 The M57 is the Yugoslavian made version of the Russian TT-33, which is based on John Browning's blowback operated FN Model 1903 (it uses Browning's short recoil dropping-barrel system from the M1911). However, it employs a much simpler hammer/sear assembly than the M1911, and the Soviet engineers also added several other features such as locking lugs all around the barrel (not just on top), and made several alterations to make the mechanism easier to maintain, notably a captive recoil spring secured to the guide rod which does not depend on the barrel bushing to hold it under tension. The Yugoslavian M57 has been popular for decades thanks to its proven track record, reliability and high quality.

The M57 is an all metal single action and is known for its precision and ease of use. It is the ideal defense weapon, as it is easy to handle and maintain. The pistol has fixed iron sights. Its handgrip covers are made of selected walnut or of polymer.

On a practical note, consider what handgun ammo is always out of stock these days: 22, 22LR, 9MM .40S&W and of course .45ACP. This firearm utilizes a FAR less popular and relatively inexpensive round that is much easier to get a hold of nowadays. You wont find people making a run on 7.62x25. Ever. For those of you who reload, Reloadable cartridge cases can be produced by resizing and trimming 9mm Winchester Magnum brass, or alternately by reforming 5.56×45mm NATO.

KEY FEATURES

Caliber: 7.62x25.

Weight: 1.94 pounds.

Arsenal, Inc., the premier American importer and manufacturer of Kalashnikov-pattern rifles and pistols, is proud to offer to the American enthusiast the Bulgarian-made SAM7K Pistol. This 7.62x39mm caliber pistol combines authentic, high-quality features rarely seen in the American market. Every component of the SAM7K is engineered to provide decades of dependable service. The SAM7K pistol is bound to become a sought-after shooter and collectible firearm.

Arsenal’s Exclusive Milled And Forged Receiver
Each SAM7K receiver is milled from a hot-die hammer forged receiver blank by the Arsenal Co. of Bulgaria. Other milled-receiver AKs are machined from bar stock, but Arsenal’s hot-die hammer forging produces stronger and finer-grained steel. Internal voids and cooling deformations are eliminated by the 5-ton hammer forging process.

Each forged receiver blank requires over 5.5 hours of milling before assembly. This forging and milling process is complex and time-intensive, but Arsenal’s meticulous attention to detail delivers a receiver of unequalled strength, precision and durability

Summary: SAM7K - 7.62x39mm caliber Pistol, milled receiver (hot-die hammer forged), short gas system, front sight block / gas block combination, 10 1/2 inch chrome lined hammer forged barrel, black polymer furniture, original pistol grip made to work with ambidextrous safety lever, and peep rear sight, scope rail. Includes one 5-round magazine, sling, oil bottle, and cleaning kit.
FEATURES
• 100% new-production parts and components.
• Bulgarian hot-die hammer forged receiver, bolt, bolt carrier and double-hook trigger
• Cold hammer-forged barrel from Arsenal’s Bulgarian factory, built on Steyr manufacturing technology
• Hard-chrome plated bore and chamber
• AK scope rail.
• Substantially extended service life over other types of assemblies.
• Ambidextrous safety lever 	  	SPECIFICATIONS
• Caliber: 7.62 x 39 mm
• Total Length: 506mm (20 in.)
• Barrel Length: 267 mm (10.5 in.)
• Weight without Magazine: 3.67kg (8 lbs.)
• Muzzle Velocity: 710 m/s (2329 fps)
• Rate of Fire (practical): 40 rds/min
• Twist Rate: 1 in 240 mm
• Effective Range: 400 m (547 yds)
• Max Effective Range: 1100 m (1480 yds)This a great gun for fun or for your future SBR build. Comes with a 5 round magazine but additional 30 round magazines are available.
